http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Woman-suffers-burns-as-LPG-cylinder-goes-off/article14021030.ece

An elderly woman, K. Surya Narayanamma (65), suffered serious burns when the LPG cylinder at her house went off in the early hours on Monday.Ms. Narayanamma and her husband, K. Apparao, were staying in a house at Chittinagar on Sorangam Road. Narayanamma did not have a clue that the LPG cylinder was leaking and the kitchen was filled in with gas.\When she came to the kitchen to prepare the morning tea and lit the stove, the room caught fire and the cylinder went off. The house was badly damaged due to the impact of the explosion, said the locals.]Hearing the sound, the neighbours rescued the couple and rushed the old woman to a hospital. However, Apparao escaped unhurt in the accident, said Two Town Circle Inspector N.V.S.K. Durga Rao.“The walls, doors and the windows have been completely damaged in the blast. Doctors said that Narayanamma suffered 40 per cent burns and is battling for life,” the CI said.A case has been registered and investigation is on.